channel.title: Error loading your profile
channel.description:
Hey guys,
Well, I was working with this today (MezzyScape 562 loading 659 v2), and I got this error 2 times in 1 day... And I don't feel like having this happen when it's online. Will this fix itself when I put it online and do the stuff to the client side, or will I have to do something to fix it :S If so please tell me! PS: It spits out no errors client sided and on the server side it does this: [code]log4j:WARN No appenders could be found for logger (org.apache.mina.filter.execut or.ExecutorFilter). log4j:WARN Please initialize the log4j system properly.[/code]
It does this every time I turn it on (doesn't give me the Error loading your profile thing on the client, just that error on server) and it doesn't give the client sided server. If anyone can help me that would be great! Thanks!
[img]http://dl.dropbox.com/u/18329363/errr.PNG[/img]
